    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We've thought about this from time to time over the years, and generally come to the conclusion that we do not want this. \r\n\r\n- Auto-update means that _we_ are taking executive decisions into people's operations. They might have staking-operations running with a lot of money. We're not comfortable making the call when to update that. \r\n- All updates do not work seamlessly. If an auto-update goes wrong, and the node fails to start up after an update, an automatic update migth cause the whole geth-fleet to go down _simultaneously_. If we have an incremental manual roll-out, the failure mode is less simultaneous. \r\n\r\n",
